company_description:
Flying Squirrel Sports - The World's Largest Indoor Trampoline Adventure Parks. Flying Squirrel was founded by two enterprising entrepreneurs Luke Schueler and Cody Schueler in 2015. 

We make it our mission to offer premier entertainment services, in so many different forms. Our parks are designed and built by the best in the industry to maximize safety. Flying Squirrel Sports trampoline park structures include: shock absorbing suspension mounts, a connection system with a pivoting bed rail and a german gas shock absorber assembly incorporated directly into the trampoline framework. The unique design allows the frames to pivot and travel up to 4 inches upon impact through the specific use of german shocks. Unlike all OTHER TRAMPOLINE PARKS which are built using straight steel frames which underlie the vinyl foam pad attached to the top. The foam pad is the only soft surface that protects the jumper from injury when landing on the trampoline frame. Flying Squirrel Sports welcomes you to the future of trampoline parks! 

We take pride in being The World's Largest Trampoline Parks with locations all over the world! International Association of Trampoline Parks 2018 IATP BRAND GROWTH AWARD & 2018 CHARITABLE CONTRIBUTION AWARD 

Canada Locations: Calgary Alberta, Hamilton Ontario, Ottawa Ontario, South Calgary Alberta, London Ontario, Winnipeg Manitoba, Victoria British Columbia, London Ontario,  Whitby Ontario, Chatham Ontario (Under Construction)
Central America: Guatemala City Guatemala, Medellin/Los Molinos Colombia, Lima Peru, San Miguel Peru, Lima Peru #2 (Under Construction) 
United States: Spokane WA, Tampa FL, Jungle Island Miami FL, Weston Miami FL, Everett Washington, Moscow Idaho, Miami Mega Park (Under Construction) Vancouver WA Mega Park (Under Construction) Coeur D'Alene Idaho (coming soon)

company_description:
WELCOME TO ILILI.

We're honored to share the cuisine and culture of Lebanon in the heart of New York City and Washington DC. Since 2007, our home in the Flatiron District has introduced the passion and generosity of the Lebanese table to hundreds of thousands of curious diners while comforting native Lebanese guests with a celebration of their homeland and values.

Owner and Executive Chef Philippe Massoud expertly crafts a sophisticated blend
of modern and traditional Lebanese cuisine drawing influences from the span of the ancient Silk Road trade routes. Flavorful herbs and spices combine to delight the palate; earthy and delicate textures emerge from innovative combinations of savory and sweet; each bite reveals a deeper story behind the birth of the Eastern Mediterranean culinary culture.

Our warm and generous hospitality drives our mission to make every guest and team member feel genuinely welcomed and fundamentally honored. We are here to share; to pass fresh pita bread and mezze amongst old friends and new; to celebrate life and its delicious bounty.

We invite you to experience our old world hospitality, timeless generosity, and tireless dedication to uncovering and sharing the rich traditions of Lebanon and the Levant.

company_description:
There's something beautiful to discover around every corner.

Rove iQ is a wayfinding software and smart kiosk company created to help move humans intelligently. Rove iQ's software solutions provide customized maps, directories and wayfinding services for smart cities, healthcare, universities, real estate and entertainment venues. 

Visitors experience that delight of discovery with Rove iQ software. With Rove iQ, businesses and organizations provide customized, 3D maps through kiosks and smartphone browsers that help visitors navigate their spaces, while also serving up additional information such as augmented reality selfies, coupons, current events and  advertising. The software provides properties with data analytics, allowing owners and managers to gain meaningful insights and generate additional digital out-of-home advertising revenue. Rove iQ creates an opportunity for all types of venues to better communicate with and engage visitors, as well as make their experiences seamless, easy and enjoyable.

Locations such as the Miami Design District in Miami, Florida, Fashion Island in Newport Beach, California and Barclays Center in Brooklyn, New York use Rove iQ to help visitors navigate their spaces and find specific locations and amenities. Beyond finding what they need, visitors often discover the unexpected and experience moments of delight, encouraging them to leverage the technology whenever they visit a Rove iQ property.

company_description:
Starting out in 2001 as Classic Catering, Dean & Debbie Young have pleased many clients over the years with their culinary and event planning talents; always going above and beyond to make everyone happy. In 2006, they opened their first special events venue, Gatherings, along with Jim & Cheryl Cox. 
In 2008, Monterey Beach Weddings was born to create a "whole" package for our Gatherings couples. In 2010, the team was able to acquire The Perry House in Monterey and has beautifully restored it as a special events facility.
The company continued to grow with us purchasing the Perry House, our beautiful venue that offers beautiful views of the Bay and a great proximity to downtown Monterey. 
In 2016, another great opportunity came with us working with the National Trust for Historic Preservation on a New Vision for the historic Cooper Molera Adobe property right in downtown Monterey. With a lot of hard work, we started to lease the newly renovated Barns at Cooper Molera, holding our first event in July of 2018! 
Yes, another opportunity presented itself as we became the proud leaseholder of what is known as the Monterey Beach House. We are looking forward to doing a few renovations on this property as well! 
With our businesses massive growth, we had to make a few hard decisions and ended up closing down our venue, Gatherings, in 2019 and stop our Monterey Beach Wedding Service as well. 
Our simple motto has always been and remains today: Great Food, Great Service, Every Time!

company_description:
Since 2003, i9 Sports®, the nation's first and largest youth sports league franchise business in the United States, has served 5 million participants at over 1,000 locations across 36 states nationwide. Based in Tampa, Florida, i9 Sports has replaced a high pressure, adult-centered experience with a child-centered model that puts fun first. Customers enjoy the i9 Sports Experience which emphasizes age-appropriate instruction that is fun for kids and convenient for today's busy families. It's the Way Youth Sports Should Be®. 

With 20 consecutive years of record-revenue, franchise owners offer youth sports programs for boys and girls in popular sports such as flag football, soccer, basketball, baseball, volleyball, tennis, and lacrosse. i9 Sports is ranked in Entrepreneur's prestigious list of top 500 franchises, featured as a top 100 Game Changer by Franchise Dictionary, and selected as a Project Play Champion by the Aspen Institute for taking meaningful actions to encourage multi-sport sampling and help grow national youth sports participation rates.

To learn more about i9 Sports youth sports programs and locations, visit www.i9sports.com. For more information on i9 Sports franchising opportunities, visit www.i9sportsfranchise.com.

company_description:
At teambuilding™ we run fun virtual team building activities for remote teams. We work with organizations all over the world, including the United States, Canada, UK, Australia and more.

Our remote team building activities include Online Office Games, Superhero Academy, Tiny Campfire, and Murder Mysteries! We also run professional development training like our Remote Storytelling Workshop and Comedy Workshop. 

Our virtual team building is designed from the ground up to connect remote workers. We use elements like ice breaker questions, breakout rooms and fun live experiences to build deep connections and create shared memories.

We also run local corporate events. For example, we run team building activities in NYC, Chicago, Los Angeles, San Francisco, Washington DC and more US cities. Our local brands for team building including Museum Hack for renegade museum tours and The Great Guac Off for a guacamole making competition you can do with your team.

We believe in the power of team building for remote teams and local teams. We believe that work can be f***ing awesome, and that when everyone is operating as part of a team you can achieve a lot together.

company_description:
Pax House is a Residential Chemical Dependency Treatment Center located beneath the majestic San Gabriel Mountains in a quiet, upscale neighborhood in Altadena, California.

Pax is the Latin word for peace. It signifies a time in history marked by an absence of war. Through the treatment process, we will introduce our clients to a way of life free from the war of addiction.

We offer a structured residential treatment program designed to provide each client with accurate information concerning the disease of addiction/alcoholism as well as exposure toward a proven path of recovery. It is our hope every client will comprehend the nature of the illness and embark upon a journey of recovery which will far exceed their expectations.

Pax House staff is committed to providing meaningful interaction with every client during their journey through the treatment process. We understand the challenges of early recovery and will serve as positive role models.  Our goal is to demonstrate a happy, fun, healthy, productive, positive life without the use of alcohol and drugs.  Each staff member reflects the success of this goal.

company_description:
Cedar Lakes Estate is a premiere wedding venue in the Hudson Valley.  Equipped with charming cottages, a rustically elegant barn, and stunning outside venues, we host weekend-long weddings as well as retreats and other special events. As a close-knit family business, we create experiences for our both our guests and employees unlike any other wedding venue. 

At Cedar Lakes, we believe in doing everything slowly and meaningfully, making everything from scratch, and creating a custom menu for each wedding. This is not your average wedding food! Our food is refined farm-to-table, using seasonal, local, and artisanal ingredients. We have a small farm on site, where we grow organic produce and make our own honey and cheese. Everything else is purchased from our neighbors in the small farm town, cultivating a network of "beyond local"​ purveyors.

We have been named one of the top 15 wedding venues by NYMag and #1 weekend wedding venue by Lover.ly. We have also been featured on all major wedding sties, including Daily Candy, Martha Stewart Weddings, Style Me Pretty, Ruffled, The Knot, Green Wedding Shoes, Well Wed, etc.

company_description:
**Welcome to The Olde Mill Inn**  
Nestled in the scenic hills of Somerset, The Olde Mill Inn blends the charm and rich history of the area with modern amenities. Conveniently located and easily accessible from all major travel points in the Tri-State area, we are close to numerous Fortune 500 corporate headquarters, shopping, local attractions, and outdoor activities to help you reconnect with nature.

**Accommodations**  
Our 102 guest rooms, including allergy-friendly PURE rooms and luxurious grand suites, are thoughtfully designed for comfort and relaxation. Each room is equipped with modern amenities such as high-speed wireless internet, Keurig coffee makers, irons and full-size ironing boards, blow dryers, and laptop safes. The stylish décor creates a peaceful environment ideal for business travelers, couples, visitors, and local guests alike.

**Meetings & Conferences**  
With over 16,000 square feet of private meeting space across 18 rooms, The Olde Mill Inn is the perfect venue for your next corporate or business event. Our flexible spaces can accommodate groups from 5 to 500 people, equipped with state-of-the-art technology to ensure your event runs smoothly. The Business Center, with full secretarial support services, is located on the meeting room level for your convenience.

**Social Events**  
Whether hosting an intimate gathering of 20 or a grand reception for 250, our unique banquet spaces offer a perfect setting for your special event. Each event room opens to a patio or deck, surrounded by beautiful gardens and lawn areas. Our dedicated event coordinators are here to assist with every detail, ensuring your event is unforgettable.

company_description:
CSz Portland is a company of creative people who perform, teach and lead with a strong foundation in improvisation and a "Yes, And..." attitude.

We work with businesses, government agencies, non-profits, groups, education and enrichment seekers and public audiences of all kinds.

We are connected to the world through CSz Worldwide (cszworldwide.com), with ComedySportz teams in 25 cities (US and Europe) and through the Applied Improvisation Network.

We offer Public and Private/Custom Shows at our Arena, Road Shows, Classes, Professional Development Training, Branded Theatre and other Creative Services. Many of these services are available online as well - we are experts in Zoom-based training.

We are flexible & easy to work with.


We play ComedySportz! About the ComedySportz Show:

ComedySportz -- Portland's longest-running show - is fast-paced, clean, family-friendly and competitive improvisational comedy. We've played every weekend since May 28, 1993.

Two teams alternate improvised scenes, games and songs, and the audience votes for the team they like better. A referee explains the rules, calls the ComedySportz fouls, and solicits suggestions from the audience to inspire every scene/game. The ref is our secret weapon - the ref keeps it moving and keeps it clean.

ComedySportz is 100 percent family and business friendly. It's a show that entertains everyone with offending anyone - our regular show audiences features bachelor parties, church groups, senior citizens, teenagers, kids and adults at the same time.

More info at cszportland.com or visit linktr.ee/CSzPortland for fast links.

company_description:
We believe that everyone deserves the mind-body experience of yoga. By connecting you to a practice that is energizing, empowering, and fun. We deliver life-enhancing benefits through our six core classes: Y6 101, Y6 Stretch, Y6 Slow Flow, Y6 Hot, Y6 Power, and Y6 Sculpt & Flow. 

Or as we say at YogaSix: Calm mind. Strong vibe. Sweat tribe. 

Yoga created boutique fitness as we know it. At YogaSix we are changing the way people think. Our yoga and fitness classes allow our members to define their own practice. We help members connect to themselves in a way that is energizing, empowering, and fun. With an established and loyal following, YogaSix is a modernized yoga brand that promote accessibility and is poised for nationwide adoption.
